      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "The main use case for `RunCommandParseJSON` is making the GUI work with hardware wallets. RPC users could in principle also call HWI manually. So one alternative to look at could be [QT process](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qprocess.html). That said, the RPC code also serves to maintain good test coverage, and we wouldn't want to pull a QT dependency into bitcoind. But maybe the QT relevant code can be extracted?\r\n\r\n> Though ideally we'd use whatever subprocess library we choose for the *notify commands as well, to be consistent.\r\n\r\nThere's that too.",
